UI_visible_response: "Cover-Up Class" is a pun that creatively combines the concept of the "proletariat," a term historically associated with the working class, with the idea of concealing or suppressing information. In this context, it humorously refers to individuals or groups who engage in covering up or hiding information, often in a political or social context. The term plays on the similarity in sound between "proletariat" and "cover-up," while also highlighting the ironic contrast between the working class and those who might have the power to manipulate or obscure the truth.
